library(gganimate)

  
sas3<-sas2 %>% group_by(provider,moa) %>% summarise(n=n(),.groups="drop")
sas4<-sas3 %>% group_by(moa) %>% mutate(rank=rank(-n)) %>% ungroup()
sas5<-sas4 %>% filter(rank<=10)

sas_animate<-sas5 %>% ggplot(aes(x=rank,
                                 y=n,
                                 group=provider,
                                 fill=provider,
                                 label=provider))+
  geom_col()+
  geom_text(aes(y=n,label=provider),hjust=1.4)+
  coord_flip(clip='off',expand=FALSE)+
  scale_x_reverse()+
  labs(title="Month: {closest_state}",x="",y="Number of People Admitted")+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 1, size = 22),
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
        axis.text.y  = element_blank()) + 
  transition_states(moa)+
  ease_aes("cubic-in-out")
animate(sas_animate,nframes=400,fps=10)

library(tidyverse)

sas2$target<-case_when(
  sas2$tot < median(sas2$tot)~"low",
  TRUE ~"high"
)
sas_predict<-sas2 %>% select("age","sex","raceethn","provider","moa","mod","admtype","campus","los","target")

sas_predict1<-sas_predict %>% filter(raceethn!="",admtype!="")

set.seed(2020)
splitIndex<-createDataPartition(sas_predict1$target,p=.05,list=FALSE)

df_train<-sas_predict1[splitIndex,]
